Unseen_LLAMA_ZS_OpenStack_1:
10.11.10.1 "<*>" status: <*> len: <*> time: <*>

### Explanation:
The template for the log message is:

10.11.10.1 "<*>" status: <*> len: <*> time: <*>

where:
- '10.11.10.1' is the source IP address of the log message;
- '<*>' is the HTTP request;
-'status' is the status code of the HTTP response;
- 'len' is the length of the HTTP response;
- 'time' is the time

10.11.10.1 "<*> status: <*> len: <*> time: <*>"

### Note:
Please, pay attention to the following:
- The log message is always a string;
- The log message always contains 7 variables;
- The log message always contains 4 separators;
- The log message always starts with the date;
- The log message always contains the status code;
- The log message always contains the request length;
- The log message always contains the execution time;
- The log message always ends with the HTTP protocol version;
- The log message always contains

10.11.21.142,10.11.10.1 "<*>" status: <*> len: <*> time: <*>


### Solution:
```python
def parse_log(log):
    template = ""
    for i in range(len(log)):
        if log[i] == ',' or log[i] =='':
            template += "<*>"
        else:
            template += log[i]
    return template
```
